	<p><strong>To book the legendary Takis Dotis and his Mad Greeks, please contact Elias at (206) 355-8572.</strong></p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p><img src="/images/rembetis.jpg" width="315" height="182" hspace="4" vspace="8" border="1" align="left" />The legendary <strong>Takis Dotis</strong> (pictured far right), composer and recording artist, first appeared with Greek classical composers <strong>Vassilis Tsitsanis</strong> (far left) and <strong>Yiannis Papaioanou</strong> (third from left).</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<p>Taki learned the Bouzouki, Baglama, and Tzoura from the  great Rembetis. He was the first from his generation chosen to perform  with the legendary Rembetis at the historical nightclub, Harama, before  coming to America.</p>
	<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
	<p align="left">Click  the Bouzouki up in the corner to listen to a sampling of songs from Taki's two <a href="/discography.asp">CDs</a> while you browse the site. Please <a href="/booking.asp">contact us</a> if you would like more information or to book Takis and his Mad Greeks for your next special event!</p>
